              <li>• Requires larger portfolio to achieve the same lifestyle spend</li>
              <li>• Assumes constant real returns over very long time horizons</li>
              <li>• Sequence of returns risk still applies in early years</li>
              <li>• Requires discipline to not overspend in good years</li>
              <li>• May be overly conservative for those with shorter life expectancies</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
